Body (Figs 1; 2
A-C
) oblong and overall appearance lustrous due to lack of punctures or microsculptures on the majority of body parts; unicolor, mostly brown, with elytra lighter and pronotal posterior part darker (the body color is much lighter when the species is alive (Fig. 6
C-D
) or the specimens are newly collected); integument scatteredly pubescent with short, thin, yellowish setae except pygidium, and the setae on pronotum are distinctly thicker and shorter.
